21/03/2004
BRATISLAVA, Slovakia -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano discussed the situation in Kosovo Friday (19 March) in separate meetings with Macedonian counterpart Branko Crvenkovski and Romanian counterpart Adrian Nastase. The talks took place on the sidelines of the conference on NATO-EU relations in Bratislava. All three leaders stressed that stability in Kosovo is crucial to regional stability. Crvenkovski said stability across the border is especially important in view of Macedonia's 14 April presidential election. In addition to Kosovo, Nano and Nastase discussed their country's NATO aspirations. (Rompres, ATA, Dnevnik - 19/03/04)
